GREATER FLAMINGO 
The word flamingo comes from the Latin word for  
flame. Greater flamingos are beautiful birds known  
for their distinctive pink plumage and their long,  
graceful necks and legs. They reach an average  
height of four feet, making them one of the tallest  
birds in the world.  
 
Greater flamingos are found all over the world. Large  
populations live in northwest India, the Middle East,  
the western Mediterranean, and Africa. Smaller  
flocks can be found scattered throughout northern  
Europe. Flamingo flocks can number in the  
thousands. 
 
